article.description: — Ansley Almonor's 22 points helped Fairleigh Dickinson defeat Sacred Heart 93-91 on Saturday.
article.headline: Almonor's 22 help Fairleigh Dickinson take down Sacred Heart 93-91
article.linkText: Almonor's 22 help Fairleigh Dickinson take down Sacred Heart 93-91
article.story: TEANECK, N.J. -- — Ansley Almonor's 22 points helped Fairleigh Dickinson defeat Sacred Heart 93-91 on Saturday. Almonor added five rebounds for the Knights (10-12, 4-3 Northeast Conference). Jo'el Emanuel scored 17 points while going 5 of 8 and 6 of 9 from the free throw line, and added five rebounds. Sean Moore had 17 points and shot 6 for 10, including 4 for 5 from beyond the arc. The Pioneers (10-12, 4-3) were led in scoring by Kyle McGee, who finished with 23 points, seven rebounds and two steals. Nico Galette added 18 points, 17 rebounds and six assists for Sacred Heart. In addition, Aidan Carpenter had 16 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
